div.p:
Miss E Gore presents her compts
compliments. to Baron von Müller and having heard from Mr Bracebridge Wilson, Geelong, that she might apply to him for spare duplicates of some of the Algae mentioned in Mr Wilson's list,
J. B. Wilson (1889). she ventures to send the names of those, she would so much like to have, if Baron von Müller could spare any.
See also E. Gore to M, 30 July 1890.

p.style: font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center;
